headline: Why AI Stock ServiceNow Got Thumped on Thursday
summary: For the second time in as many days, ServiceNow (NYSE: NOW) was hit with an analyst price target cut on Thursday.  The Thursday cut was delivered by Deutsche Bank's Brad Zelnick.  Uncomfortably, news of this came less than 24 hours after Zelnick's peer Derrick Wood of TD Cowen made a nearly identical move.
